[SN]TITLE[SN]
51 new jobs announced for Limavady, Coleraine and Kilrea

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
51 new jobs have been announced for seven companies in Limavady, Coleraine and Kilrea.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
They are in a range of sectors including textiles, food, construction, information technology and engineering.
Enterprise Trade and Investment Minister Jonathan Bell said it is a combined investment of Â£3m across seven local companies.
Mr Bell said that the jobs are across a wide range of roles and industries.
"This substantial investment is testament to the commitment and drive of these companies to prosper and grow, and will enhance their overall competitiveness in an ever challenging marketplace.
"With Invest NI support, these businesses will drive exports and deliver excellent benefits not only to the local area but to the wider Northern Ireland economy."
